  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this experiment is to investigate the effect of video game playing for 30
      minutes on food intake and subjective appetite. The investigators hypothesize that video
      game playing will affect food intake in children. Food intake will be measured at 30 minutes
      following a glucose (50g glucose in 250ml of water) or sweetened non-caloric (150mg
      SucraloseÂ® in 250ml of water) beverage with or without video game playing. Subjective
      appetite will be measured at 0, 20, 35 and 65 minutes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
